  <h2>Process layout</h2>
  <p>Four launchd plists in <code>ops/launchd/</code> bring up the system:</p>
  <ul>
    <li><strong>daemon</strong> — the live scheduler (APScheduler) that runs every cron job in §12.</li>
    <li><strong>lab</strong> — independent scheduler for the research loop (§9).</li>
    <li><strong>dashboard</strong> — FastAPI UI that reads <code>state.db</code> read-only.</li>
    <li><strong>supervisor</strong> — restarts any of the above on watchdog failure (<code>watchdog_account.py</code>, <code>watchdog_stall.py</code>).</li>
  </ul>

  {{ callout("info", "Why one orchestrator for three workflows?",
     "All three live workflows share <code>RiskManager</code> and <code>DecisionStore</code>, which means a per-strategy halt or a global gross/net cap applies across them in one place. <code>TradeOrchestrator.scan</code> reads the asset class from the candidate and picks the right gate path, but the envelope is shared.") }}
